三、我的觀點：<BR>
     The book is woven with many short stories looking like pieces of puzzles. Each story is short and tiny seemingly, but great and meaningful actually. This is a story that tells a young man is searching for the gift, which also symbolizes his journey of growth. When the young man was a little boy, a wise old man told him there was a special gift in the world. If the young man got the gift, his life could become more colorful, carefree and successful. However, only could the young man receive the gift all on his own. Then, the young man tried his utmost to search for the gift which could make his life more abundant. Still, the more desperately he looked for the gift, the less happy he felt. Until the young man decided to put down all things, and stopped blindly looking for the gift, did he realize the gift he was seeking after was always around him.<br />
<br />
     The most impressive part of the story is the experiences the young man got while he was pursuing the gift. In order to make his life more successful and rich, the young man blindly sought after the gift. On his way to the goal, he always lost his direction. Sometimes it seemed that he almost got his desirable gift, but eventually found out it was nothing but a dream. However, it did not mean that the young man got nothing on his way to look for the gift. Every time when he stumbled, he learned a new lesson from the failure. When he put down all things and got rid of his desire, he realized the most valuable thing was not the gift itself but the experiences and lessons he acquired on his journey through life. The whole book is like someone’s life story which makes me think a lot about my own life. In addition, not only do some regrettable experiences flash into my mind, but I restart to reflect on myself.<br />
<br />
     This unforgettable event occurred at the age of fifteen. I stared my high school life in a private vocational school in Kaohsiung. Nevertheless, the tuition was so steep that my single mother could not afford it. Not for long, I decided to drop out for a year to make some tuition and help my mom to relieve financial burden. During that period, I lived with my grandma in mountain areas of Kaohsiung. In order to make much more money, I worked hard all day and all night. I took a few part-time jobs at the same time, rebuilt the mountain trails and helped in my neighbor’s farmland almost every day. Though I made plenty of money at that time, I apparently ignored my grandma. One day, my grandma was sick. She required me to stay with her for a day. I chatted with her, shared what had happened during my work time, and helped her to clean and water the plants in her yard. Meanwhile, she also taught me some tips to care for the plants. Not knowing why, I was in a cheerful mood that I had never been in after moving there. All of a sudden, I realized that the most precious gift I was eager to get was not money but happiness foe my lovely family members. The gift I sought after for a long time was literally pretty simple and always by my side.<br />
<br />
     From this experience, I learn that when we pursue fame and wealth, we may ignore people or things that are originally significant for us. True happiness is always around us. Disillusioned with the occupation and desire, we may miss plain happiness in our daily lives. Nonetheless, only when we give up restless and endless pursuit, can we relax and discover “the present”. As I join the journey of the young man, I come to realize how simple happiness can be. Sometimes I recall good days with my grandma in Kaohsiung. This memory reminds me that time flies, and we should cherish all we have now. Most important of all, we should seize the day, trusting as little as possible in the future. What we do now decides what the future will be like.<br />
<br />

<BR>
四、討論議題：<BR>
     Is it worth of sacrificing plain happiness in pursuit of fame and fortune?<br />
